<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" standalone="yes"?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><channel><title>Sigterm on ErrorCode — Error Code Reference &amp; Solutions</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/tags/sigterm/</link><description>Recent content in Sigterm on ErrorCode — Error Code Reference &amp; Solutions</description><generator>Hugo</generator><language>en</language><atom:link href="https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/tags/sigterm/index.xml" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"/><item><title>[Solution] Bash Trap: Invalid Signal Specification Error Fix</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/bash/bash-trap-signal-error/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/bash/bash-trap-signal-error/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="bash-trap-invalid-signal-specification-error-fix"&gt;Bash Trap: Invalid Signal Specification Error Fix&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A bash trap signal error occurs when you specify an invalid signal name or number in the &lt;code&gt;trap&lt;/code&gt; command.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="what-this-error-means"&gt;What This Error Means&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The &lt;code&gt;trap&lt;/code&gt; command registers handlers for signals. If you provide a signal name that doesn&amp;rsquo;t exist (e.g., &lt;code&gt;SIGTYPO&lt;/code&gt;), bash reports &amp;ldquo;invalid signal specification.&amp;rdquo;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="common-causes"&gt;Common Causes&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Typo in signal name (e.g., &lt;code&gt;SIGINTT&lt;/code&gt; instead of &lt;code&gt;SIGINT&lt;/code&gt;)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Using wrong signal number&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Using platform-specific signals not available on all systems&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Missing signal name argument&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2 id="how-to-fix"&gt;How to Fix&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h3 id="1-use-correct-signal-names"&gt;1. Use correct signal names&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# WRONG: Typo in signal name&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;trap &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#39;echo &amp;#34;caught&amp;#34;&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt; SIGINTT
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# CORRECT: Use valid signal name&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;trap &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#39;echo &amp;#34;caught&amp;#34;&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt; SIGINT
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="2-list-available-signals"&gt;2. List available signals&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Check available signals&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;kill -l
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Use numeric signal codes&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;trap &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#39;echo &amp;#34;caught&amp;#34;&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;2&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# SIGINT&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="3-handle-common-signals-properly"&gt;3. Handle common signals properly&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# CORRECT: Handle common signals&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;cleanup&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;()&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;{&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; rm -f /tmp/lockfile
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; echo &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;Cleaned up&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;}&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;trap cleanup EXIT INT TERM
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="4-use-err-for-error-handling"&gt;4. Use ERR for error handling&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# CORRECT: Trap errors&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;trap &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#39;echo &amp;#34;Error on line $LINENO&amp;#34;&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt; ERR
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;set -e
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 id="related-errors"&gt;Related Errors&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="signal-trap"&gt;Signal Trap&lt;/a&gt; — signal handling behavior&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="return-code"&gt;Return Code&lt;/a&gt; — exit status handling&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="command-not-found"&gt;Command Not Found&lt;/a&gt; — missing commands&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;</description></item><item><title>[Solution] PHP Error 128 — SIGTERM Script Terminated Fix</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/php/error-128/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/php/error-128/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="solution-php-error-128--sigterm-script-terminated-fix"&gt;[Solution] PHP Error 128 — SIGTERM Script Terminated Fix&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;PHP error code 128 indicates the script was terminated by a &lt;code&gt;SIGTERM&lt;/code&gt; (signal 15) from an external source. This is not a PHP error itself — it means the operating system or a process manager killed the PHP process. PHP exit codes are calculated as &lt;code&gt;128 + signal number&lt;/code&gt;, so &lt;code&gt;128 + 15 = 143&lt;/code&gt; for SIGTERM, but error 128 specifically reflects the base exit code when the process receives a termination signal.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>[Solution] Ruby SignalException — Signal Handling Fix</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/ruby/signal-exception/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/ruby/signal-exception/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="signalexception--signal-handling-fix"&gt;SignalException — Signal Handling Fix&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A &lt;code&gt;SignalException&lt;/code&gt; is raised when a signal is received by the Ruby process. &lt;code&gt;Interrupt&lt;/code&gt; is a subclass raised by &lt;code&gt;SIGINT&lt;/code&gt; (Ctrl+C).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="description"&gt;Description&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;code&gt;SignalException&lt;/code&gt; is the parent class for signal-related exceptions. When the process receives a signal (like &lt;code&gt;SIGTERM&lt;/code&gt;, &lt;code&gt;SIGINT&lt;/code&gt;, &lt;code&gt;SIGHUP&lt;/code&gt;), Ruby raises &lt;code&gt;SignalException&lt;/code&gt;. The &lt;code&gt;Interrupt&lt;/code&gt; class is a specific subclass for &lt;code&gt;SIGINT&lt;/code&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Common scenarios:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;SIGTERM&lt;/strong&gt; — graceful shutdown signal from process managers.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;SIGINT&lt;/strong&gt; — user interrupt (Ctrl+C).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;SIGHUP&lt;/strong&gt; — terminal hangup, often used for config reload.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;SIGUSR1/SIGUSR2&lt;/strong&gt; — user-defined signals for custom actions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2 id="common-causes"&gt;Common Causes&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-ruby" data-lang="ruby"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Cause 1: Default signal handling&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Most signals have default handlers that terminate the process&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Cause 2: Custom signal handlers that raise&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;Signal&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;trap(&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;USR1&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;) { &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;raise&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;SignalException&lt;/span&gt;, &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;USR1&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt; }
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Cause 3: Unhandled signals&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# If no handler is set, default behavior applies&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Cause 4: Signal during critical section&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Signal arrives while holding a lock&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 id="solutions"&gt;Solutions&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h3 id="fix-1-handle-specific-signals"&gt;Fix 1: Handle specific signals&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-ruby" data-lang="ruby"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;Signal&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;trap(&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;TERM&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;) { puts &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;Received SIGTERM, shutting down...&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;; exit &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;0&lt;/span&gt; }
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;Signal&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;trap(&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;INT&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;) { puts &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;Received SIGINT, shutting down...&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;; exit &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;0&lt;/span&gt; }
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;Signal&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;trap(&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;HUP&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;) { reload_config }
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;Signal&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;trap(&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;USR1&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;) { rotate_logs }
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="fix-2-use-graceful-shutdown-pattern"&gt;Fix 2: Use graceful shutdown pattern&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-ruby" data-lang="ruby"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;@running &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;true&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;Signal&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;trap(&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;TERM&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;) { @running &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;false&lt;/span&gt; }
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;Signal&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;trap(&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;INT&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;) { @running &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;false&lt;/span&gt; }
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;while&lt;/span&gt; @running
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; process_next_item
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; sleep &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;0&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;1&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;end&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;puts &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;Shutting down gracefully...&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;cleanup
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="fix-3-block-signals-during-critical-sections"&gt;Fix 3: Block signals during critical sections&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-ruby" data-lang="ruby"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;def&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;critical_operation&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; mutex &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;Mutex&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;new
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;Signal&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;trap(&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;USR1&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;) &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;do&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; mutex&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;synchronize { perform_action }
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;end&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; mutex&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;synchronize &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;do&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; perform_sensitive_operation
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;end&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;end&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="fix-4-handle-signals-with-cleanup"&gt;Fix 4: Handle signals with cleanup&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-ruby" data-lang="ruby"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;Signal&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;trap(&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;INT&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;) &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;do&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;begin&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; cleanup
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;rescue&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt; e
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; puts &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;Error during cleanup: &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;#{&lt;/span&gt;e&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;message&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;}&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;end&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; exit &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;0&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;end&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 id="related-errors"&gt;Related Errors&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="interrupt"&gt;Interrupt&lt;/a&gt; — SIGINT (Ctrl+C) specifically.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="systemexit"&gt;SystemExit&lt;/a&gt; — program exit via &lt;code&gt;exit&lt;/code&gt; method.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="broken-pipe"&gt;Errno::EPIPE&lt;/a&gt; — broken pipe (related to SIGPIPE).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;</description></item></channel></rss>